  "page": "Donnel Hill/Theories",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"right\" width=\"180px\" style=\"float:right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center; background-color:#c2c2c2; font-size:12px; -moz-border-radius-topleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-topright:10px;\">&#160;Theories&#160;may&#160;be&#160;removed&#160;if&#160;...&#160;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-size:11px; text-align: left; background-color:#eeeeee; font-weight:lighter;-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-bottomright:10px;padding-right: 1em; padding-left: .5em; padding-right: .5em;\">\n<ol><li>Stated as questions or possibilities.</li>\n<li>More appropriate for another article.</li>\n<li>Illogical or previously disproven.</li>\n<li>Proven by canon source, and moved to main page.</li>\n<li>Speculative and lacking any evidence to support arguments.</li>\n<li>Responding to another theory (use <a href=\"/index.php?title=Talk:Donnel_Hill/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Talk:Donnel Hill/Theories (page does not exist)\">discussion page</a> instead).</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><ul><li><small>This does not include responses that are also standalone theories.</small></li>\n<li><small>Usage of an indented bullet does not imply the statement is a response.</small></li></ul></dd></dl>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Hill\" title=\"Donnel Hill\">Donnel Hill</a> is theorized to be a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy\" title=\"Bastardy\">bastard</a> son of <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Supporting_evidence\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Supporting evidence</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Evidence_against\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence against</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Supporting_evidence\">Supporting evidence</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Donnel_Hill/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Supporting evidence\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>He himself claims to be a bastard of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Tywin is known to have sex with <a href=\"/index.php/Prostitution\" title=\"Prostitution\">prostitutes</a>, as with <a href=\"/index.php/Shae\" title=\"Shae\">Shae</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos77.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos77.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li>Additionally, <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> states that a <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> ordered the construction of a secret passageway to <a href=\"/index.php/Chataya%27s_brothel\" title=\"Chataya&#39;s brothel\">Chataya's brothel</a>, the same brothel that the yellow-haired and green-eyed prostitute <a href=\"/index.php/Marei\" title=\"Marei\">Marei</a> works at.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>\n<li>He has physical and characteristic similarities to other Lannisters of Tywin's line.\n<ul><li>He has yellow hair that he wears down in a tumble, a common trait of the Lannisters of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>He has fat lips, a trait he shares with <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>He makes easy japes, a trait he shares with <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>\n<li>When asked if Tywin had any bastard offspring, <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> did not deny this possibility, merely answering that <i>\"[Tywin]'d have you flogged for the mere suggestion.\"</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_against\">Evidence against</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Donnel_Hill/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence against\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>No character in the books ever mentions the existence of an acknowledged bastard son of Tywin.</li>\n<li>Given the above-quoted answer by George R. R. Martin, it is likely that Tywin would never acknowledge a bastard child as his own.</li>\n<li>It is possible that Donnel Hill is a son of another member of House Lannister.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Donnel_Hill/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Marei/Theories\" title=\"Marei/Theories\">Marei/Theories</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister/Theories\" title=\"Tywin Lannister/Theories\">Tywin Lannister/Theories</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Donnel_Hill/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Prologue\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Prologue\">Prologue</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos77.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos77.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_77\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 77\">Chapter 77</a>, Tyrion XI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_15\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 15\">Chapter 15</a>, Tyrion III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/Various_questions_concerning_Tywin_Oberyn_Gregor_the_North_and_Sansa\">Tywin, Oberyn, Gregor, The North, and Sansa (April 15, 2008)</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404200116\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.026 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.027 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 373/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8776/10